                  , about the hour of seven at night, on the <rs id="t17851214-89-cd413" type="crimeDate">21st day of October</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17851214-89-off412 t17851214-89-cd413"></join> last, and burglariously stealing therein one wooden till, value 4 d. five shillings, and two hundred and thirty-five pieces of copper money, called halfpence, the property of the said 
                     <persName id="t17851214-89-person834">
                        James
                         Clarke
                     <interp inst="t17851214-89-person834" type="surname" value="Clarke"></interp>
